news.title: Recover 90% property tax dues in this fiscal year, Haryana government tells MCG
news.para: The civic body could generate only 13% of the projected income from property tax — Rs 165 crore — against its target of Rs 1,235 crore in 2021-22.

news.title: Visakhapatnam: Prices fixed for middle income group layouts
news.para: The prices range between 14,000 to 18,000 per square yard for the plots in four layouts that are being carved out in Anandapuram mandal in Vizag suburbs.

news.title: Jaipur development body panel to monitor lease deed distribution
news.para: The members of the committee will go for surprise monitoring at camps, look for progress reports from officials and guide officials wherever required.

news.title: Cluster redevelopment now must for all Mhada layouts across Maharashtra
news.para: A state government resolution (GR) making cluster redevelopment mandatory in Mhada layouts issued on Thursday states that redevelopment of a single Mhada building will be allowed only in exceptional circumstances.

news.title: LIC to unlock value of its huge real estate assets
news.para: The MD of the insurance behemoth, Siddhartha Mohanty, who was in the city for the IPO roadshow of LIC, said that the state-run insurer is gradually taking back its properties. LIC has real estate assets in Mumbai, Kolkata and other metro cities.

news.title: Mumbai-based realtor sent to CBI custody till May 6 in Yes Bank-DHFL case
news.para: ​Chhabriaa of Radius Developers was arrested by the Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) on Thursday. The central probe agency produced him before special judge S H Gwalani and sought his 14-day custody for further probe into the matter.

news.title: Haryana CM orders immediate MCG takeover of nine colonies
news.para: With the takeover, the civic issues of these colonies — which are currently being taken care of by the respective developers — will come under the jurisdiction of the MCG.

news.title: Gurugram: Before handover, builder has to carry out safety audit 3-4 times
news.para: At the concluding session of SEWOCON, chief minister Manohar Lal Khattar addressed RWA representatives and launched a booklet on structural safety.

news.title: Mumbai: Realtor fails to pay penal interest on home delay, Rs 3 crore flat to be auctioned
news.para: ​The home buyer complained to MahaRERA after the promoter failed to deliver possession of the flat. MahaRERA ordered the promoter to pay interest to the home buyer, till the possession of the flat was handed over.

news.title: Smartworks leases 2.3 lakh sq ft space in Bengaluru
news.para: Smartworks currently has a growing footprint of approx. 7 Mn sq. ft. with a presence in 10 cities and 37 centres. caters to over 450 organisations across Forbes 2000 companies, MNCs, and unicorns.

news.title: UltraTech Cement's net profit rises 47% to Rs 2,613.75 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: As per the company, UltraTech Cement has now become a Rs 50,000 crore turnover company and the first Indian cement company to achieve this milestone.

news.title: Concrete jungles sprout as rules eased in Tamil Nadu
news.para: According to the old norms, if plot size (within Directorate of Town and Country Planning limits) exceeded 2,500 square metres, 10% of land should be handed over to local bodies through a gift deed.

news.title: Telangana: SCDRC jails builder for cheating flat buyers
news.para: The commission bench, comprising president Justice MSK Jaiswal, members Meena Ramanathan and K Ranga Rao, pronounced this order after hearing an execution plea filed by Dr R Renuka, her daughter, and son, who were aggrieved with the loss of money invested by her late husband R Eswari Prasad for buying a flat with Gharonda Builders and Developers.

news.title: After HC order, Chandigarh housing board gives seven days to remove violations
news.para: A senior CHB official said four structures were demolished on Wednesday and two on Thursday. UT director public relations (DPR) Rajiv Tewari was duty magistrate for the demolition exercise, he said.

news.title: Tamil Nadu government will increase supply of Valimai cement: Official
news.para: Speaking to reporters on the sidelines of the event, Tancem general manager Narmatha Devi said the government was increasing the supply of Valimai cement in the open market, since the price of private cement brands were rising.
